Class LinkedSequence<E>

java.lang.Object
  cs2321.LinkedSequence<E>
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<E>, net.datastructures.Deque<E>, net.datastructures.IndexList<E>, net.datastructures.PositionList<E>, net.datastructures.Sequence<E>
public class LinkedSequence<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements net.datastructures.Sequence<E>

Linked list implementation of the Sequence interface. The iterators returned by this interface are complete copies of the data in the structure at the time of the iterator's creation. Note that elements may be of any type, including null. Course: CS2321 Section ALL Assignment: #3 - Linked Sequence

Author:
Bill Siever
